  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Itezhitezhi Rural Livelihood Improvement Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">People living in the Itezhitezhi district of Zambia face short periods of food surpluses followed by months of food shortages because they are unable to preserve the surplus food or sell it at a profit when it is available. Many depend on forest products such as wild mushrooms or roots and tubers during periods of shortage but these are being threatened by logging and woodland clearance for cultivation. In the neighbouring district of Choma a food processing and marketing project has increased household incomes, nutrition and self-confidence. This project aims to gather the information necessary to introduce a similar project in Itezhitezhi.</narrative>
  </description>
